test-method.description: HADRS Precheckin test 1. Create a cluster with HA(default settings) and DRS(in automatic mode) enabled. 2. Create vm-1 on host-1, move host-1into cluster and check for HA configuration on host-1. 3. Power-on vm-1. This should fail with AdmissionControlCheckFailed. 4. Turn-off the admission control and power-on vm-1. 5. Turn-on the admission control and check the cluster to be red. 6. Configure host-1 as failover host. 7. Power-off vm-1 and enter host-1 into maintenance mode.8. Move host-1 out of the cluster. This should fail as host-1 is failover host. 9. Exit host-1from maintenance mode. 10. Move host-2 into cluster and check for HA configuration. 11. Power-on vm-1 on host-1, this vm should be relocated by DRS and should be powered-on on host-2. 12. Enter host-2 into maintenance mode. This should fail with a DRS insufficient resources fault 13. Reconfigure the cluster with admission control off and enter host-2 into maintenance mode. 14. vm-1 should be migrated by DRS and the enter maintenance mode should be successful. 15. Reconfigure the cluster with admission control on and host-1 as the failover host. The powered-on vm should be migrated to host-2 16. Power-off vm-1 and enter host-1 into maintenance mode and move the hosts out of the cluster. 17. Destroy vm-1 and the cluster.
